1
00:00:06,372 --> 00:00:09,175
(PANTING)

2
00:00:09,275 --> 00:00:11,845
[MAN] CATCH YOUR
BREATH THERE, BOY.

3
00:00:11,945 --> 00:00:13,914
(BOY EXHALES)

4
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:15,415
[MAN] LOOKS LIKE
IT'S EAST.

5
00:00:15,516 --> 00:00:18,885
HEY, POPS, HAVE
YOU EVER SEEN AN
ADVENTURER UP CLOSE?

6
00:00:18,985 --> 00:00:20,621
[POPS] HMPH.

7
00:00:20,721 --> 00:00:23,724
[BOY] I HEARD A RUMOR
ONCE THAT AN ADVENTURER
YOUNGER THAN ME

8
00:00:23,824 --> 00:00:27,193
SKIPPED RIGHT OVER THIS
MOUNTAIN, HUMMING A TUNE.

9
00:00:27,293 --> 00:00:29,863
I'D REALLY LOVE TO BE ABLE
TO DO SOMETHING LIKE THAT!

10
00:00:29,963 --> 00:00:31,665
[POPS] DON'T BOTHER.

11
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:33,366
WHAT CAN THEY DO?

12
00:00:33,466 --> 00:00:36,369
CAN THEY LIVE AS ONE
WITH THE LAND?

13
00:00:36,469 --> 00:00:38,905
ADVENTURERS CREATE NOTHING.

14
00:00:39,005 --> 00:00:41,608
THEY SIMPLY FIGHT
AND SHED BLOOD.

15
00:00:42,943 --> 00:00:44,010
HUH?

16
00:00:44,110 --> 00:00:45,746
[BOY] WHAT IS IT, POPS?
[POPS] SHH.

17
00:00:45,846 --> 00:00:47,213
[BOY] OHH...

18
00:00:48,782 --> 00:00:52,385
(DISTANT RUMBLING)

19
00:00:52,485 --> 00:00:54,487
[POPS] OH, NO.

20
00:00:54,588 --> 00:00:55,656
THAT LOOKS BAD.

21
00:00:55,756 --> 00:00:59,492
WE HAVE TO GET BACK
AND TELL THE VILLAGE.

22
00:00:59,593 --> 00:01:01,394
(WHIMPERING)

23
00:02:42,529 --> 00:02:44,798
[SMASH]
AH, HERE YOU GO!

24
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:51,471
(NYAN‐TA WHISTLES)

25
00:02:52,138 --> 00:02:53,574
[NYAN‐TA] OH, YEAH!

26
00:02:53,674 --> 00:02:57,778
I DEFINITELY NEED TO BRING
THE WHOLE GUILD HERE NEXT TIME.

27
00:03:05,051 --> 00:03:06,252
(TOYA GRUNTS)

28
00:03:06,352 --> 00:03:08,054
COME GET SOME!

29
00:03:08,154 --> 00:03:09,890
HEAD SPLITTER!

30
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:11,091
I DID IT!

31
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:14,427
(ELECTRICAL SOUND)
HUH? HEY, I'M STUCK!

32
00:03:15,295 --> 00:03:16,329
HELP ME!

33
00:03:16,429 --> 00:03:18,532
PURIFICATION BARRIER!

34
00:03:18,632 --> 00:03:20,200
[TOYA] HUH?!

35
00:03:21,101 --> 00:03:23,003
ASSASSINATION!

36
00:03:23,103 --> 00:03:24,270
AURA SABER!

37
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:25,839
[TOYA] UHH...

38
00:03:25,939 --> 00:03:27,407
[MINORI] HUH...

39
00:03:28,308 --> 00:03:29,843
[TOYA]
SORRY, GUYS. I, UH‐

40
00:03:29,943 --> 00:03:32,613
[NAOTSUGU] SAMURAI ATTACKS HAVE
A LONG COOL DOWN, LITTLE MAN.

41
00:03:32,713 --> 00:03:36,182
AND AFTER YOU CAST A
STRONG SPELL, YOU MIGHT
NOT BE ABLE TO MOVE.

42
00:03:36,282 --> 00:03:37,618
BET YOU FORGOT ABOUT THAT.

43
00:03:37,718 --> 00:03:40,053
[TOYA] I REMEMBERED IT,
REALLY. I JUST...

44
00:03:40,153 --> 00:03:42,989
SHIROE ASKED US TO
WATCH OUT FOR YOU
DURING YOUR TRAINING.

45
00:03:43,089 --> 00:03:44,390
DON'T EXPECT US
TO GO EASY ON YOU.

46
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:46,459
[TOYA AND MINORI]
THANK YOU, SENSEI.

47
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,794
[NAOTSUGU]
NEXT TOPIC.

48
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:50,731
MAN TO MAN, TOYA.
YOU SEE, CHICKS ARE LIKE‐

49
00:03:50,831 --> 00:03:52,332
(NAOTSUGU WAILS)

50
00:03:52,432 --> 00:03:55,168
[TOYA] LIKE WHAT?
[AKATSUKI] NAOTSUGU IS A MORON.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

51
00:03:55,268 --> 00:03:56,537
[MINORI] SENSEI...

52
00:03:56,637 --> 00:03:58,271
[NAOTSUGU] AS FOR YOU, MINORI,
WE'LL DO OUR BEST,

53
00:03:58,371 --> 00:04:01,975
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHAT
WE CAN TEACH YOU ABOUT
BEING A SHRINE PRIEST.

54
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,276
[MINORI] THAT'S OK.

55
00:04:03,376 --> 00:04:06,279
HE TOLD ME EVERYTHING
I NEED TO KNOW.

56
00:04:06,379 --> 00:04:08,081
(GRUMBLES)

57
00:04:08,181 --> 00:04:09,382
[NYAN‐TA] SHIROECHI?

58
00:04:09,482 --> 00:04:10,817
[SHIROE] UH, HEY, CHIEF.

59
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:13,820
YOU PULLED YOURSELF ANOTHER
ALL‐NIGHTER, DIDN'T YOU?

60
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:16,690
NOT TRUE. I MANAGED
A LITTLE BIT OF SLEEP.

61
00:04:16,790 --> 00:04:18,659
[NYAN‐TA] TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF THE NICE DAY.

62
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:22,228
GO OUTSIDE. DO SOMETHING
ELSE FOR A WHILE.

63
00:04:22,328 --> 00:04:24,998
SEE SOME OF
AKIHABARA'S NEW STUFF.

64
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:28,969
[SHIROE] I'D LOVE TO,
BUT I'VE GOT OTHER THINGS
OCCUPYING MY MIND RIGHT NOW.

65
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:32,338
[NYAN‐TA] AND BY THAT,
YOU MEAN SOME WAY TO
GET US ALL HOME, HUH?

66
00:04:32,438 --> 00:04:33,907
YEAH, THAT, TOO.

67
00:04:34,007 --> 00:04:36,543
BUT EVEN IN A WORLD LIKE THIS
THAT USED TO BE A GAME FOR US,

68
00:04:36,643 --> 00:04:39,580
THAT OLD SAYING ABOUT KNOWLEDGE
BEING POWER STILL WORKS.

69
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,782
[NYAN‐TA] WHAT DO YOU
HAVE HERE, HMM?

70
00:04:41,882 --> 00:04:44,585
[SHIROE] IF A COOK PREPARES
FOOD WITH HIS OWN HANDS,

71
00:04:44,685 --> 00:04:48,121
AND A CRAFTSMAN MAKES
THINGS WITH NOTHING BUT
TOOLS AND HIS WITS,

72
00:04:48,221 --> 00:04:51,858
THEN WE'VE ALREADY SEEN
THAT WE CAN DO THINGS
THE GAME NEVER COULD.

73
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:55,195
[NYAN‐TA] AH, SO YOU'RE
TRYING TO SEE IF YOU
CAN GET THE SAME RESULTS

74
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,664
FROM YOUR SKILLS
AS A SCRIBE, HUH?

75
00:04:57,764 --> 00:05:00,000
I WAS ABLE TO DRAW UP
A SIMPLE CONTRACT.

76
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:03,336
I WONDER IF THERE ARE
OTHER APPLICATIONS FOR IT.

77
00:05:03,436 --> 00:05:05,171
(CHIME)
HMM?

78
00:05:05,271 --> 00:05:06,573
HEY, HENRIETTA.

79
00:05:06,673 --> 00:05:09,242
[HENRIETTA]
SHIROE, I CAN'T
HANDLE THIS ANYMORE!

80
00:05:09,342 --> 00:05:10,911
SAVE ME!

81
00:05:11,011 --> 00:05:11,945
[SHIROE] HUH?

82
00:05:12,045 --> 00:05:13,580
I WANT TO GO!
I WANT TO GO!

83
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,248
[MARIELLE] I WANT TO EAT!
[SHIROE] OH, WOW.
[HENRIETTA] UGH!

84
00:05:15,348 --> 00:05:17,250
SO I GUESS ALL OF US
GOT A CALL, HUH?

85
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:18,719
[TOYA] SURE DID, MAN.

86
00:05:18,819 --> 00:05:20,386
[NYAN‐TA] ALL RIGHT, WHAT'S
ALL THE COMMOTION IN HERE?

87
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:21,755
WELL, IT'S KIND OF LIKE‐

88
00:05:21,855 --> 00:05:22,789
IT'S SUMMER.

89
00:05:22,889 --> 00:05:25,425
IT'S SUMMER IN THE
ELDER TALES WORLD!

90
00:05:25,526 --> 00:05:26,893
AND SUMMER IS ALL
ABOUT THE BEACH,

91
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:30,564
SNOW CONES, WATERMELON,
RAMEN, AND CURRY RICE!

92
00:05:30,664 --> 00:05:32,265
LIKE, TOTALLY, RIGHT?

93
00:05:32,365 --> 00:05:33,900
LET ME GO TO THE BEACH!

94
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,002
[MARIELLE] I WANT TO
HAVE A SNOW CONE...
[HENRIETTA] STOP THIS!

95
00:05:36,102 --> 00:05:39,840
THE CRESCENT MOON ALLIANCE
IS ONE OF THE ROUND TABLE'S
11 ESTEEMED GUILDS,

96
00:05:39,940 --> 00:05:42,242
AND YOU ARE SUPPOSED
TO BE ITS GUILD MASTER.

97
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:43,610
(MARIELLE WHIMPERS)

98
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:45,912
LOOKS LIKE AKIHABARA STILL
HAS A LOT OF PROBLEMS.

99
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:49,816
WE PROBABLY SHOULDN'T LEAVE
IT RIGHT NOW, SHOULD WE?

100
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:52,385
[MARIELLE]
I'VE WORKED REALLY HARD.

101
00:05:52,485 --> 00:05:54,921
(CRYING) I'M STILL
WORKING REALLY HARD!

102
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:59,092
ALL I REALLY WANT IS SOME
REST AND RECREATION!

103
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:01,194
[HENRIETTA] YOU COME DOWN HERE
THIS INSTANT, MARIELLE!
[NYAN‐TA] I WOULD DARE SAY

104
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:05,398
THAT THE LADY IS IN A
RATHER DIRE NEED OF A
CHANGE OF PACE, HMM?

105
00:06:05,498 --> 00:06:07,568
THE BEACH, HUH?

106
00:06:09,603 --> 00:06:12,539
[ISUZU] WHAT'S THIS?
A NEW QUEST?

107
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:14,741
OK, WAIT.
HOLD ON A SECOND.

108
00:06:14,841 --> 00:06:18,044
"ROUND TABLE‐SPONSORED TRAINING
CAMP FOR NEW PLAYERS"?

109
00:06:18,144 --> 00:06:21,114
[PLAYER] A SUMMER
TRAINING CAMP FOR NEW
PLAYERS UNDER LEVEL 40?

110
00:06:21,214 --> 00:06:25,719
HOW DELIGHTFULLY
BOURGEOIS OF OUR NEW
LEVEL‐90 BENEFACTORS.

111
00:06:25,819 --> 00:06:28,855
HUH! HA HA HA!

112
00:06:28,955 --> 00:06:33,827
IT'S TIME! THEY FINALLY
CREATED A STAGE LARGE
ENOUGH TO ACCOMMODATE ME.

113
00:06:33,927 --> 00:06:37,063
AT LONG LAST, EVERYONE
WILL WITNESS MY PROWESS!

114
00:06:37,163 --> 00:06:42,669
EVERYONE WILL BOW
TO THE MAGNIFICENT NAME
"RUNDELLHAUS CODE"!

115
00:06:42,769 --> 00:06:44,571
[MARIELLE]
THIS IS A SUPER IDEA.

116
00:06:44,671 --> 00:06:47,373
[HENRIETTA]
IT'S PERFECT EXCUSE
FOR A VACATION.

117
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:49,242
[MARIELLE]
BEACH TRAINING CAMP!

118
00:06:49,342 --> 00:06:50,544
[HENRIETTA] MARIELLE!

119
00:06:50,644 --> 00:06:52,012
WE WERE TALKING
ABOUT TRAINING NOOBS,

120
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:54,515
AND MARIELLE NEEDED TO GET
OUT OF THE GUILD BUILDING.

121
00:06:54,615 --> 00:06:56,082
TWO BIRDS,
ONE STONE, BRO.

122
00:06:56,182 --> 00:06:59,452
FOR DARK, SINISTER SHIROE,
COMING UP WITH A PLAN LIKE THIS

123
00:06:59,553 --> 00:07:02,222
IS REALLY NO
BIG DEAL AT ALL.

124
00:07:02,322 --> 00:07:04,591
[SHIROE]
"DARK, SINISTER SHIROE"?

125
00:07:04,691 --> 00:07:06,693
YOU'RE A GOOD,
"SINISTER," SHIROE...

126
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:09,763
AND SO ARE YOU, BIG,
STRONG NAOTSUGU!
[NAOTSUGU] AH, GET OFF OF ME!

127
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:12,533
[NYAN‐TA] SO WILL YOU
BE GOING, AS WELL, HMM?

128
00:07:12,633 --> 00:07:14,467
[SERARA]
YES, I AM.

129
00:07:14,568 --> 00:07:17,871
UM... I DON'T SUPPOSE
YOU ARE, TOO?

130
00:07:17,971 --> 00:07:21,775
I WILL BE ASSISTING THE OTHERS
WITH YOUR TRAINING PROGRAM, DIG?

131
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:23,376
(FAWNING)

132
00:07:23,476 --> 00:07:25,311
[ALL]
SHE'S SO OBVIOUS.

133
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:27,981
[NYAN‐TA] COOL.

134
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:31,117
[TOYA] SHIROE AND ALL HIS
FRIENDS ARE GONNA BE THERE.

135
00:07:31,217 --> 00:07:32,385
[MINORI] YEAH.

136
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:34,521
[TOYA] I'VE GOT TO DO
THE BEST I CAN. HA!

137
00:07:34,621 --> 00:07:36,256
[TOYA] YAH!

138
00:07:36,356 --> 00:07:40,527
[MINORI, THINKING]
I GUESS PART OF ME WAS
ALWAYS DOWN ON MYSELF

139
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:43,263
FOR NOT BEING ABLE TO
DO ANYTHING FOR TOYA.

140
00:07:43,363 --> 00:07:48,001
I REALLY THOUGHT THERE WAS
SOMETHING I COULD'VE DONE
OR SHOULD'VE DONE FOR HIM,

141
00:07:48,101 --> 00:07:51,572
AND I JUST COULDN'T OR
DIDN'T KNOW HOW TO DO IT.

142
00:07:51,672 --> 00:07:53,974
BUT THAT JUST ISN'T
THE CASE ANYMORE.

143
00:07:54,074 --> 00:07:56,142
NOW IT'S UP TO ME TO
MAKE SURE SHIROE KNOWS

144
00:07:56,242 --> 00:08:00,647
HE DID THE RIGHT THING BY
SAVING US AND LETTING
US JOIN HIS GUILD.

145
00:08:00,747 --> 00:08:02,482
HMM.

146
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:08,421
[KAYU]
MAN, NOTHING'S
BITING TODAY.

147
00:08:08,522 --> 00:08:09,823
HUH?

148
00:08:09,923 --> 00:08:11,925
(HOOFBEATS)

149
00:08:12,025 --> 00:08:14,127
WHAT'S GOING ON?

150
00:08:14,227 --> 00:08:17,598
[AKATSUKI] SO THIS IS
WHERE THE TRAINING CAMP
WILL BE HELD, MY LORD?

151
00:08:17,698 --> 00:08:20,701
[SHIROE]
THE TOWN OF CHOSHI IN
THE ZANTLEAF REGION.

152
00:08:20,801 --> 00:08:23,003
[HENRIETTA]
KARASHIN HAS ALREADY GONE
AND LOOKED AT THE AREA,

153
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:27,273
AND HE HAS ALREADY MANAGED
TO SPEAK WITH THE PEOPLE
OF THE LAND THERE, AS WELL.

154
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:29,009
WAY TO HANDLE
BUSINESS, MAN.

155
00:08:29,109 --> 00:08:31,945
[HENRIETTA] SHORYU OF
OUR GUILD AND REZARICK
FROM THE BLACK SWORDS

156
00:08:32,045 --> 00:08:33,747
WILL BE PARTICIPATING
AS TRAINERS.

157
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,682
[SHIROE] THAT'S FINE, BUT‐
[NAOTSUGU] UH.

158
00:08:35,782 --> 00:08:38,585
NOW ALL I NEED IS SOME SPF
50 TO KEEP THE SUN OFF!

159
00:08:38,685 --> 00:08:40,186
IT'S TOO
EARLY FOR THAT.

160
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:42,288
YOU KNOW THE CAMP ISN'T
UNTIL NEXT MONTH, MARIELLE.

161
00:08:42,388 --> 00:08:45,926
I HAVE A SUMMER DRESS FOR YOU,
MY DARLING AKATSUKI!
[AKATSUKI] OH, COME ON!

162
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:47,761
[NAOTSUGU] MAYBE WE NEED
TO PUSH UP THE DATE.

163
00:08:47,861 --> 00:08:49,696
[SHIROE] YOU MAY BE RIGHT.
[HENRIETTA] I SWEAR IT!

164
00:08:49,796 --> 00:08:51,397
(SHORYU GASPS)
(CHIME)

165
00:08:51,497 --> 00:08:53,366
[HENRIETTA]
DID YOU FIND SUNSCREEN?

166
00:08:53,466 --> 00:08:56,937
[SHIROE] NO. THERE WERE A LOT
OF PEOPLE OUTSIDE THE GATES
I HADN'T SEEN BEFORE.

167
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:58,471
[HENRIETTA] HUH?

168
00:08:58,572 --> 00:09:00,073
[MAN 1] WHAT IS GOING ON?

169
00:09:00,173 --> 00:09:02,509
[MAN 2] DO YOU REMEMBER
THINGS LIKE THIS IN THE GAME?

170
00:09:02,609 --> 00:09:04,010
[MAN 1] NO, NOT REALLY.

171
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:06,279
[SHORYU] THAT'S THEM.
[NAOTSUGU] YEAH, OK.

172
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:11,317
LIKE, WHY DOES THAT DUDE
WITH THE FUNKY HAT
LOOK FAMILIAR TO ME?

173
00:09:11,417 --> 00:09:12,686
[NAOTSUGU] WHAT THE HECK?

174
00:09:12,786 --> 00:09:14,888
[AKATSUKI] WHAT'S
GOING ON, MY LORD?

175
00:09:14,988 --> 00:09:16,857
[SHIROE] THEY'RE ALL
PEOPLE OF THE LAND.

176
00:09:16,957 --> 00:09:18,892
[MARIELLE]
SO THAT MEANS...

177
00:09:18,992 --> 00:09:21,227
[SHIROE]
A HERALD OF ROYALTY.

178
00:09:23,063 --> 00:09:26,099
[HERALD] I AM THE EMISSARY
OF DUKE SERJIAD COWEN,

179
00:09:26,199 --> 00:09:29,469
HIGH LORD OF EASTAL'S
LEAGUE OF FREEDOM CITIES.

180
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:35,942
I HAVE COME HERE TO GAIN
AUDIENCE WITH THE LEADER OF
THE ROUND TABLE CONFERENCE.

181
00:09:36,042 --> 00:09:39,880
[SHIROE, VOICE‐OVER]
IN "ELDER TALES,"
JAPAN IS CALLED YAMATO.

182
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:43,483
IT'S DIVIDED INTO
5 MAJOR TERRITORIES.

183
00:09:43,584 --> 00:09:45,852
THE LEAGUE OF FREEDOM
CITIES OF EASTAL

184
00:09:45,952 --> 00:09:49,289
IS AN ALLIANCE OF LORDS
THAT RULE EASTERN JAPAN,

185
00:09:49,389 --> 00:09:54,127
AND EASTAL HAS SENT AN
EMISSARY TO THE ROUND TABLE.

186
00:09:54,227 --> 00:09:57,698
THEY WANT US TO ATTEND
THEIR NEXT GATHERING
OF ALLIED NOBLES,

187
00:09:57,798 --> 00:10:00,934
AND CURIOUSLY, THERE'S
ALSO A DANCE INVOLVED.

188
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:02,102
(HOOFBEATS)

189
00:10:02,202 --> 00:10:04,605
[KRUSTY] AND I SUPPOSE YOU
ANTICIPATED THIS, TOO?

190
00:10:04,705 --> 00:10:09,876
[SHIROE] THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND
SHOULD BE WELL AWARE OF OUR
ESTABLISHING THE ROUND TABLE.

191
00:10:09,976 --> 00:10:12,513
SO, YES, THIS MOVE
ISN'T UNEXPECTED.

192
00:10:12,613 --> 00:10:16,917
THEY SAID THEY WERE
PREPARED TO GRANT TITLES
OF NOBILITY TO SOME OF US.

193
00:10:17,017 --> 00:10:19,019
IT'S NOT AN
EASY CHOICE,

194
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:21,788
WHETHER OR NOT WE GO THERE
TO REPRESENT OURSELVES.

195
00:10:21,888 --> 00:10:23,456
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
NOT EASY?

196
00:10:23,557 --> 00:10:26,827
OBVIOUSLY WE CAN
START NETWORKING WITH
THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND,

197
00:10:26,927 --> 00:10:28,662
AND WE SHOULDN'T PASS IT UP,

198
00:10:28,762 --> 00:10:32,398
ESPECIALLY WHEN THERE'S A
CHANCE TO LEARN MORE ABOUT
THIS WORLD THAN WE DO.

199
00:10:32,498 --> 00:10:34,167
SO WHAT'S THE DOWNSIDE?

200
00:10:34,267 --> 00:10:38,371
[SHIROE] WE MAY VERY WELL GET
CAUGHT UP IN THEIR POLITICS.

201
00:10:38,471 --> 00:10:42,175
IF WE DON'T PARTICIPATE, THAT
POSSIBILITY GOES AWAY, BUT...

202
00:10:42,275 --> 00:10:45,879
[KRUSTY] WE LOSE A CHANCE
TO GAIN VALUABLE INFORMATION.

203
00:10:45,979 --> 00:10:48,181
[SHIROE]
THAT'S THE TRADEOFF.

204
00:10:48,281 --> 00:10:50,951
[KRUSTY] IS THERE A CHANCE
OF WAR WITH THEM?

205
00:10:51,618 --> 00:10:53,319
[SHIROE]
IT'S NOT LIKELY.

206
00:10:53,419 --> 00:10:55,021
THERE'S NO ONE IN THEIR
RANKS THAT WE KNOW OF

207
00:10:55,121 --> 00:10:57,724
WHO'S ANYWHERE NEAR AS
STRONG AS AN ADVENTURER...

208
00:10:57,824 --> 00:11:00,126
CERTAINLY NOT LEVEL 90s LIKE US.

209
00:11:00,226 --> 00:11:01,227
[KRUSTY] ALL RIGHT.

210
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:04,430
SO WHAT DO YOU HAVE
IN MIND? I'M LISTENING.

211
00:11:04,931 --> 00:11:06,833
HMM.

212
00:11:19,212 --> 00:11:22,348
[MARIELLE] OHH, I CAN SMELL
THE SALT ON THE AIR!

213
00:11:22,448 --> 00:11:25,085
[NAOTSUGU] IT'S WAY DIFFERENT
FROM AKIHABARA, ISN'T IT?

214
00:11:25,185 --> 00:11:28,054
[TOYA] CHECK IT
OUT, MINORI. THERE!

215
00:11:28,154 --> 00:11:30,090
[MINORI] WOW!

216
00:11:31,157 --> 00:11:32,726
[NYAN‐TA] HMM.

217
00:11:32,826 --> 00:11:35,529
SOME TREES, BUT MOSTLY
MEADOW AROUND HERE.

218
00:11:35,629 --> 00:11:36,963
[SERARA] YEAH!

219
00:11:38,164 --> 00:11:39,966
[TOYA] OH, YEAH.
THOSE LOOK GOOD!

220
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:43,036
[MINORI] NOW, TOYA, DON'T
TAKE ANY WITHOUT ASKING.

221
00:11:43,136 --> 00:11:44,871
THAT WOULD BE
SIMPLY VULGAR,

222
00:11:44,971 --> 00:11:46,472
BUT WHAT DO YOU EXPECT
FROM COMMONERS?

223
00:11:46,573 --> 00:11:49,175
[TOYA] WHAT'D YOU SAY?!
[MINORI] TAKE IT EASY, TOYA.

224
00:11:49,275 --> 00:11:51,712
[ISUZU] YOU'RE AS
LIVELY AS EVER, I SEE.

225
00:11:51,812 --> 00:11:53,413
[MINORI]
HEY, ISUZU!

226
00:11:53,514 --> 00:11:55,215
YOU KNOW, BACK IN
THE REAL WORLD,

227
00:11:55,315 --> 00:11:58,151
