HOLDING A TRAINING CAMP
INSIDE THE GAME LIKE THIS.

228
00:11:58,251 --> 00:11:59,452
(MINORI LAUGHS)

229
00:11:59,553 --> 00:12:01,121
[MINORI AND TOYA] HUH?

230
00:12:01,221 --> 00:12:04,625
[TOYA] IS SHE ONE OF
THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND
WHO LIVE AROUND HERE?

231
00:12:04,725 --> 00:12:07,260
[ALL] HI!

232
00:12:12,999 --> 00:12:15,368
[TOYA]
ARE THEY SERIOUS?!

233
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:17,470
[ISUZU]
ISN'T THIS A SCHOOL?

234
00:12:17,571 --> 00:12:20,206
THIS IS WHERE WE'RE
GONNA BE STAYING
EVERY NIGHT? AWESOME!

235
00:12:20,306 --> 00:12:23,510
AND TONIGHT WE'RE HAVING
A BARBECUE OUTSIDE!
(CROWD CHEERS)

236
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:27,113
[TOYA] I SURE WISH
BROTHER SHIROE WOULD'VE
COME WITH US, MINORI.

237
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:28,915
[MINORI] YEAH.

238
00:12:29,015 --> 00:12:32,819
HE HAS AN IMPORTANT CONFERENCE
WITH ONE OF THE GOVERNMENTS
OF THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND.

239
00:12:32,919 --> 00:12:34,988
[MINORI]
HE'S GOT TO BE THERE.

240
00:12:36,156 --> 00:12:38,391
I WONDER IF THE KIDS IN
CAMP ARE DOING OK.

241
00:12:38,491 --> 00:12:42,996
HEY, I LEFT MY BRAND‐NEW
STEAM ENGINE BEHIND TO
GO ON THIS TRIP OF YOURS.

242
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:45,532
[MICHITAKA] KEEP YOUR HEAD
IN THE GAME, MASTERMIND.

243
00:12:45,632 --> 00:12:47,934
[SHIROE]
OK. I GOT IT.

244
00:12:48,034 --> 00:12:49,870
[KARASHIN]
I UNDERSTAND.

245
00:12:49,970 --> 00:12:51,271
WE NEED TO SEND A PARTY THERE

246
00:12:51,371 --> 00:12:53,574
TO SEE IF WE CAN GET MORE
INFORMATION ABOUT THEM.

247
00:12:53,674 --> 00:12:56,710
[ISAAC] IT'S REALLY CUTE THAT
THEY WANT TO MAKE US NOBLES,

248
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:59,045
LIKE THEY'RE BETTER THAN
US IN THE FIRST PLACE.

249
00:12:59,145 --> 00:13:00,781
WHO DOES THOSE NPC'S
THINK THEY ARE?

250
00:13:00,881 --> 00:13:04,084
FOR ONE THING,
THEY'RE NOT JUST
SOFTWARE ANYMORE.

251
00:13:04,184 --> 00:13:07,187
I THOUGHT WE
DISCUSSED THAT FACT
AT LENGTH ALREADY.

252
00:13:07,287 --> 00:13:09,389
[ISAAC]
SORRY. IT'S JUST HABIT.

253
00:13:09,489 --> 00:13:12,325
[SHIROE] WE'RE ALL IN
AGREEMENT ABOUT GOING TO
THE CONFERENCE IN EASTAL.

254
00:13:12,425 --> 00:13:15,929
WE SHOULD BE SURE TO PUT
OUR BEST FOOT FORWARD
WHILE WE'RE THERE.

255
00:13:16,029 --> 00:13:18,164
SO WHO'S GONNA REPRESENT
US AT THE MEETING?

256
00:13:18,264 --> 00:13:21,367
THOSE DAYS OVERLAP WITH
THE TRAINING CAMP, YOU KNOW.

257
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:25,105
UH, I'M IN CHARGE OF THAT
TRAINING CAMP, SO I'M OUT.

258
00:13:25,205 --> 00:13:28,041
[KARASHIN] WELL, SINCE D. D. D.
HAS THE MOST MEMBERS IN IT,

259
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,744
MAYBE KRUSTY SHOULD
REPRESENT US.

260
00:13:30,844 --> 00:13:32,012
OK.

261
00:13:32,112 --> 00:13:34,247
BUT D. D. D. ARE
PRIMARILY WARRIORS.

262
00:13:34,347 --> 00:13:36,216
CRAFTING AND COMMERCE
SHOULD GO, TOO.

263
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:37,651
(KARASHIN GASPS)

264
00:13:37,751 --> 00:13:39,886
[RODERICK] UH, YOU SEE,
WE'RE WORKING ON THE
OCTOPEDE RIGHT NOW

265
00:13:39,986 --> 00:13:41,588
AND THE STEAM ENGINE TO RUN IT.

266
00:13:41,688 --> 00:13:43,824
[KARASHIN] YEAH, AND I'VE
GOT A LOT OF OTHER STUFF
GOING ON MYSELF.

267
00:13:43,924 --> 00:13:47,160
[MICHITAKA] AND I'M JUST GETTING
TO THE PART WHERE I MAKE
THIS THING MORE POWERFUL.

268
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:48,161
AN IMPASSE.

269
00:13:48,261 --> 00:13:50,296
THERE'S ONLY ONE THING
TO DO ABOUT IT.

270
00:13:50,396 --> 00:13:51,932
[ALL] ROCK, PAPER...

271
00:13:52,032 --> 00:13:53,333
[MICHITAKA] OH, CRAP.

272
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:55,502
[RODERICK] HA! YEAH!
AHEM, IT'S DECIDED, THEN.

273
00:13:55,602 --> 00:13:57,871
[KARASHIN] MICHITAKA WILL
REPRESENT THE MERCHANT GUILDS.

274
00:13:57,971 --> 00:13:59,272
[MARIELLE]
THAT WAS NICE OF HIM.

275
00:13:59,372 --> 00:14:01,775
[KRUSTY] NO. THE TEAM'S
NOT COMPLETE YET.

276
00:14:01,875 --> 00:14:05,946
I NEED SOMEONE WITH A KNACK
FOR POLITICS AND STUDYING
THE OPPOSITION.

277
00:14:06,046 --> 00:14:07,447
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

278
00:14:07,548 --> 00:14:08,649
[ALL] STARE...

279
00:14:08,749 --> 00:14:11,051
[SHIROE] OK. I GOT IT.
[AKATSUKI] HMM.

280
00:14:11,151 --> 00:14:12,786
SO THAT'S
WHAT HAPPENED?

281
00:14:12,886 --> 00:14:15,455
[SHIROE] YOU ALWAYS HAVE
THE OPTION OF BEING
A TRAINER AT THE CAMP.

282
00:14:15,556 --> 00:14:18,725
A SHINOBI SHOULD
FOLLOW HER MASTER NO
MATTER WHERE HE GOES.

283
00:14:18,825 --> 00:14:19,960
[SHIROE] REALLY, NOW?

284
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,529
AND WHY EXACTLY ARE
YOU HERE, HENRIETTA?

285
00:14:22,629 --> 00:14:23,864
[HENRIETTA]
I TOLD YOU...

286
00:14:23,964 --> 00:14:26,166
I AM MERELY
PARTICIPATING AS
AN OBSERVER.

287
00:14:26,266 --> 00:14:28,969
[SHIROE]
OK, MISS OBSERVER, SO WHAT'S
STICKING OUT OF YOUR BAG?

288
00:14:29,069 --> 00:14:30,203
(HENRIETTA GASPS)

289
00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:32,205
[HENRIETTA] OH, UH,
JUST SOME FABRIC.

290
00:14:32,305 --> 00:14:35,075
IT MOST DEFINITELY IS NOT
A SUMMER DRESS FOR AKATSUKI!

291
00:14:35,175 --> 00:14:37,844
[SHIROE] METHINKS THE LADY
DOTH PROTEST TOO MUCH.

292
00:14:37,944 --> 00:14:39,245
YOU SLY DOG, YOU.

293
00:14:39,345 --> 00:14:41,014
MAN, SHIROE,
HOW DO YOU DO IT?

294
00:14:41,114 --> 00:14:42,816
[SHIROE] IT ISN'T
LIKE THAT, GUYS.

295
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:46,019
[KRUSTY] SO TELL ME,
WHAT INFORMATION ARE WE
CULLING FROM THESE PEOPLE?

296
00:14:46,119 --> 00:14:48,354
SOME THINGS HAVE TO
HAVE MORE VALUE.

297
00:14:48,454 --> 00:14:50,624
[SHIROE] EVERYTHING
WE CAN, I GUESS.

298
00:14:50,724 --> 00:14:52,392
BUT IF I HAD TO
SET A PRIORITY,

299
00:14:52,492 --> 00:14:55,128
IT'D BE ON WHETHER OR NOT
THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND
HAVE CHANGED AT ALL.

300
00:14:55,228 --> 00:14:56,930
[MICHITAKA]
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

301
00:14:57,030 --> 00:15:00,166
BACK IN THE DAYS WHEN
ELDER TALES WAS NOTHING
BUT A GAME ENVIRONMENT,

302
00:15:00,266 --> 00:15:02,536
THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND
WERE MADE BY THE
SOFTWARE DEVELOPERS

303
00:15:02,636 --> 00:15:06,106
TO BE A WHOLE LOT WEAKER
THAN THE ADVENTURERS.

304
00:15:06,206 --> 00:15:08,074
NOW, OF COURSE, THERE
WERE IN‐GAME EXCEPTIONS

305
00:15:08,174 --> 00:15:10,410
LIKE THE PRECURSORS
AND THE ROYAL GUARD,

306
00:15:10,511 --> 00:15:13,947
BUT RUN‐OF‐THE‐MILL NPCs
NEVER GOT STRONGER THAN
THE SOFTWARE LET THEM.

307
00:15:14,047 --> 00:15:18,318
[MICHITAKA] WHEN ADVENTURERS
LIKE US DIE, WE JUST COME
BACK TO LIFE IN THE CATHEDRAL,

308
00:15:18,418 --> 00:15:21,254
BUT PEOPLE OF THE LAND
BITE IT FOR GOOD.

309
00:15:21,354 --> 00:15:24,057
[SHIROE] SO FAR, BUT WE CAN'T
BE SURE IF THE APOCALYPSE

310
00:15:24,157 --> 00:15:25,992
HAS CHANGED THEM, AS WELL,

311
00:15:26,092 --> 00:15:28,361
LIKE THE REST OF THIS "GAME."

312
00:15:28,461 --> 00:15:30,964
[MARIELLE] SORRY TO DRAG YOU
ALONG WITH ME LIKE THIS.

313
00:15:31,064 --> 00:15:32,766
[MINORI] NO, IT'S FINE.

314
00:15:32,866 --> 00:15:36,102
[SHIROE] FOR ONE THING,
THEY AREN'T SIMPLE
NON‐PLAYER CHARACTERS ANYMORE.

315
00:15:36,202 --> 00:15:37,971
THEIR EVOLUTION IS OBVIOUS.

316
00:15:38,071 --> 00:15:40,206
NPC'S WERE A PROGRAMMED
PART OF THE GAME

317
00:15:40,306 --> 00:15:42,208
DESIGNED TO HELP SEND
THE PLAYER ON QUESTS

318
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:45,746
THAT RESULT IN A PLAYER
RECEIVING GOLD, INVENTORY ITEMS,

319
00:15:45,846 --> 00:15:47,047
AND OTHER THINGS OF VALUE.

320
00:15:47,147 --> 00:15:48,915
THE MAGIC BAG IS
ONE OF THOSE THINGS.

321
00:15:49,015 --> 00:15:52,753
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE THE
REWARD FOR ONE OF THE
BASIC QUESTS EVERYONE DOES.

322
00:15:52,853 --> 00:15:54,454
IT HOLDS EVERYTHING.

323
00:15:54,555 --> 00:15:56,623
HOWEVER, FROM THE LOOKS OF IT,
PEOPLE OF THE LAND

324
00:15:56,723 --> 00:16:00,794
ARE NO LONGER GIVING ANY QUESTS
TO ANY ADVENTURERS ANYMORE.

325
00:16:00,894 --> 00:16:03,363
[MISA] AND THAT MEANS
NONE OF THE NEW PLAYERS
WILL BE ABLE TO DO

326
00:16:03,463 --> 00:16:07,433
EVEN THE SIMPLEST
QUESTS TO GET THEIR
INVENTORIES KICKSTARTED.

327
00:16:07,534 --> 00:16:11,204
[SHIROE] THE POTENTIAL
BACKLASH FROM THAT COULD BE
EXTREMELY FAR‐REACHING.

328
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:13,674
[HENRIETTA] DID YOU TELL
MARIELLE ABOUT THIS?

329
00:16:13,774 --> 00:16:15,108
[SHIROE] YEAH, I DID.

330
00:16:15,208 --> 00:16:17,778
UH, WE'RE FACT‐FINDING?

331
00:16:17,878 --> 00:16:19,345
[MARIELLE]
YEAH, SHIROE ASKED ME.

332
00:16:19,445 --> 00:16:22,182
HE SAID TO "TALK TO
THE PEOPLE OF THE LAND

333
00:16:22,282 --> 00:16:24,885
AND LEARN AS MUCH AS YOU
CAN BY TALKING TO THEM..."

334
00:16:24,985 --> 00:16:26,419
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

335
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:29,089
[MINORI] OH. SO THAT'S WHY YOU
SPOKE TO THE VILLAGE ELDER?

336
00:16:29,189 --> 00:16:30,557
[MARIELLE] WELL, THAT
WASN'T THE ONLY REASON.

337
00:16:30,657 --> 00:16:32,893
WHEN YOU THINK ABOUT IT,
I WAS JUST BEING POLITE.

338
00:16:32,993 --> 00:16:37,097
THAT'S ONE WORTH NOTING...
SO SHIROE SENT YOU.

339
00:16:37,197 --> 00:16:39,866
OH, WE DEFINITELY CAN'T
MESS THIS UP, THEN!

340
00:16:39,966 --> 00:16:42,068
[MARIELLE] YOU'RE A
GOOD GIRL, YOU KNOW THAT?

341
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:43,637
[MINORI]
WHAT'S THAT FOR?!

342
00:16:43,737 --> 00:16:45,305
[MARIELLE]
OH, I FELT LIKE IT.

343
00:16:45,405 --> 00:16:47,473
[MINORI] WHOA! HEY,
BACK OFF! THAT HURTS!

344
00:16:47,574 --> 00:16:49,175
[MARIELLE] YOU ARE JUST
ADORABLE, LIKE‐

345
00:16:49,275 --> 00:16:50,977
ANYWAY, WE'RE DONE
GREETING EVERYBODY.

346
00:16:51,077 --> 00:16:52,746
[MINORI] HUH?

347
00:16:54,047 --> 00:16:57,417
(GIGGLING)

348
00:16:57,518 --> 00:16:59,352
[MINORI] YEAH!

349
00:17:00,053 --> 00:17:02,122
NOTHING BEATS THE BEACH!

350
00:17:02,222 --> 00:17:04,791
[NAOTSUGU] CANNONBALL!
[TOYA] WHOO‐HOO!

351
00:17:04,891 --> 00:17:05,759
(GIRLS SHRIEK)

352
00:17:05,859 --> 00:17:07,160
DARN IT, TOYA!

353
00:17:07,260 --> 00:17:08,695
THAT WAS ACTUALLY
A JACKKNIFE.

354
00:17:08,795 --> 00:17:09,896
WHAT THE...?

355
00:17:09,996 --> 00:17:11,832
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING, RUNDELL?

356
00:17:11,932 --> 00:17:15,702
[RUNDELLHAUS] EVERYONE,
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE FULLY
STRETCHED OUT FOR THE WATER?

357
00:17:15,802 --> 00:17:19,372
IF YOU UNDERESTIMATE
THE SEA, BAD THINGS
CAN HAPPEN TO YOU.

358
00:17:19,472 --> 00:17:22,375
[TOYA] (GARGLED)
TRANSLATION... RUNDELL
DOESN'T KNOW HOW TO SWIM.

359
00:17:22,475 --> 00:17:24,511
[RUNDELLHAUS] PREPOSTEROUS!

360
00:17:24,611 --> 00:17:25,712
HUH!

361
00:17:25,812 --> 00:17:27,714
PEOPLE, LISTEN WELL.

362
00:17:27,814 --> 00:17:32,986
MY BEAUTIFUL SWIMMING HAS BEEN
COMPARED TO THE LEAPING OF THE
MOST GRACEFUL DOLPHINS!

363
00:17:33,086 --> 00:17:34,988
BEHOL‐ OHH!

364
00:17:35,088 --> 00:17:36,857
DEAR GOD!

365
00:17:36,957 --> 00:17:38,992
(RUNDELLHAUS SCREAMING)
[NYAN‐TA]
HERE YOU GO, BEAUTIFUL.

366
00:17:39,092 --> 00:17:40,827
[MARIELLE] YOU'RE A GEM.

367
00:17:40,927 --> 00:17:44,364
[MINORI] UM, MARIELLE, ABOUT
WHAT WE FOUND OUT EARLIER...

368
00:17:44,464 --> 00:17:47,100
LATER, MINORI.
TIME FOR THE BEACH.

369
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:50,203
[MARIELLE] ENJOY YOURSELF
JUST LIKE I AM.

370
00:17:52,706 --> 00:17:53,373
OHH.

371
00:17:53,473 --> 00:17:54,975
NOW, AIN'T THAT
A SIGHT?

372
00:17:55,075 --> 00:17:56,409
[KAYU]
BOSS, IT'S AWESOME!

373
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:59,279
SERIOUSLY! I MEAN,
LOOK AT THIS PLACE!

